<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,222,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="452">
Known from two localities in the western part of the Eastern Cape Province, and a number of sites in the far southwest of the Western Cape (
<bibRefCitation author="Bistrom" box="[512,794,258,283]" pageId="11" pageNumber="452" refString="Bistrom, O. &amp; Nilsson, A. N. (2006) Taxonomic revision of the Ethiopian genus Canthyporus (Coleoptera Dytiscidae). Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 85, 209 - 306. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4081 / memorieSEI. 2006.209" type="journal article" year="2006">
Biström &amp; Nilsson 
<number box="[733,794,258,283]" pageId="11" pageNumber="452" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). I can add the following records, which extend the range far to the north, into the Northern Cape. This species can be found in running water, but in my experience is most abundant in shallow mossy swamps, with or without seepage flow: 
<date box="[945,1067,330,355]" pageId="11" pageNumber="452" value="2008-09-27">
<number box="[945,972,330,355]" pageId="11" pageNumber="452" value="27.0">27</number>
/ix/ 
